-- Australia's major banks close Sydney CBD branches due to hostage crisis
-- By Swati Pandey
-- Sun Dec 14, 2014 09:42PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Commonwealth Bank of Australia <CBA.AX>, Westpac Banking Corp <WBC.AX> and Australia and New Zealand Banking Group <ANZ.AX>  said they had shut their Sydney CBD branches on Monday after a number of hostages were taken in a central city cafe.

"Due to the police operation in Martin Place Sydney, 12 Westpac branches in Sydney CBD will be closed for the rest of today," Westpac said in a tweet. CBA and ANZ posted similar messages.